@startuml
!include ../../style.puml

title Utilization Constraint

actor "Clients" as clients
box "Disk" #LightCyan
  queue "Queue" as queue
  database "Storage" as disk
end box

' [step1 {"name":"Arrivals & Throughput"}]
clients -> queue: Arrive (λ) = 1000 IOPS
queue -> disk: Dequeue & Write
note over disk: S (svctm) = 0.5ms\n(0.0005s)
disk --> clients: Ack (Throughput X)
note over clients, disk: Because the system is stable:\nX = λ = 1000 IOPS (r/s + w/s)
' [/step1]

' [step2 {"name":"Utilization Formula"}]
note over queue, disk #LightBlue
  **Utilization (U)**
  U = X x S
  (iostat: %util)
end note
' [/step2]

' [step3 {"name":"Current Utilization"}]
note over queue, disk #LightGreen
  At X = 1000 IOPS:
  U = 1000 x 0.0005 = 0.50
  System is 50% busy (%util = 50.00)
end note
' [/step3]

' [step4 {"name":"The Capacity Limit"}]
note over queue, disk #FFCCCC
  **The Absolute Limit**
  U cannot exceed 1.0 (%util = 100.00)
  Max Throughput (X_max) = 1 / S
  X_max = 1 / 0.0005 = 2000 IOPS
end note
' [/step4]

@enduml
